                     ARTHUR EDWARD POWELL (27)






                           PLEADED GUILTY
                      to forging and uttering an order for 21l. 3s.; 



                     also an authority for the payment of 1l.;



                     also an order for the payment of 2l. 10s. 7d.; 



                     also to embezzling the sums of 1l., 17l. 2s. 7d., and 2l. 9s. 7d., of 



                        Thomas Dawson, and another, his master; 



                     also the sums of 2l. 17s. 4l., 9s. 8d., and 15s.; 


                     also 4l. 13s., 1l. 13s., and 12l. 13s. 1d., of his said master's. 

He received a good character.—Recommended to mercy by the prosecutors.—


                        Six Days' Imprisonment.
